Acumatica ERP Construction Edition includes the following functionality:[anchor|#_57afeebc-6e23-4ea8-be78-dd3d244cf2c1] *Project accounting by cost codes. The cost codes functionality is available if the ''Cost Codes'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. *Project change management. The change orders functionality is available if the ''Change Orders'' feature is enabled on the on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form. *Stored material tracking in project pro forma invoices. The functionality is available if the ''Construction'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form. *Retainage support. The following functionality is available if the ''Retainage Support'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form: **Ability to account for retainage in commitments (purchase orders and subcontracts) and in Accounts Payable documents **Ability to account for retainage in project invoices, which include the draft invoices (pro forma) and Accounts Receivable invoices *Construction package. The following functionality is available if the ''Construction feature'' is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form: **[[#_b407f85c-05d7-4fb4-af77-0f557f42c4ba|Subcontract management] **[[#_80e4cbb0-cd29-400a-af88-61ba345aac59|Compliance tracking] **[[#_0eec01d4-da58-4594-bf01-38e3618e0b1f|Construction-specific reports]
For more information on particular features, see the respective chapter of this document. {br}{TOC}[anchor|#_371526d2-967e-4cea-ac5d-6172b428d32f] ==Project Task Types== A project task can be of the following types that can be set either on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_20_00|Project Tasks] ([~/?ScreenId=PM302000|PM302000]) form or on the '''Tasks''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] ([~/?ScreenId=PM301000|PM301000]) form:[anchor|#_764c769d-72dc-45bc-a020-cd150c183482] *'''Cost Task''' - tasks of this type are visible on the '''Cost Budget''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] form only. *'''Revenue Task''' - tasks of this type are visible on the '''Revenue Budget''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] form only. *'''Cost and Revenue Task''' - tasks of this type are visible both on the '''Revenue Budget''' and '''Cost Budget''' tabs of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] form. [anchor|#_b407f85c-05d7-4fb4-af77-0f557f42c4ba] ==Subcontract Management== Subcontract is a document that represents a commitment with a vendor to provide goods and services for a project. Subcontract workflow is similar to the workflow of a purchase order that contains service lines and non-stock lines only. AP bills are entered directly for a subcontract once the work has been completed and the AP document has been received from the vendor.{br}
Subcontracts are entered on the [HelpRoot_Construction\SC_30_10_00|Subcontracts] ([~/?ScreenId=SC301000|SC301000]) form. Subcontract lines can be linked to projects by a complex key of project, project task, inventory ID, cost code in the same way as the lines of purchase orders on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form.{br}
Subcontract entity is based on purchase order of ''Normal'' type and inherits its common functionality:[anchor|#_0bcae16e-35c4-4c65-b64b-a97dc9c35f78] *Ability to enter prepayments for subcontracts. *Ability to enter partial AP bills for subcontracts. *Ability to complete or cancel subcontracts fully or line by line. *Support for document workflow options: **Ability to approve or reject subcontracts using the standard assignment and approval maps rules. **Ability to email subcontracts. **Ability to print subcontracts. *Support for other options consistent with purchase order functionality: **Tracking as project commitments. **Change order functionality for project commitments. **Compliance tracking. **Tax calculation. **Vendor prices.
Subcontracts have the following specifics:[anchor|#_61a8e8af-c4ca-4b67-8625-7b820cef842b] *Subcontracts do not utilize stock items and do not involve inventory management processes. *Vendor-specific printed formats can be defined for subcontracts and purchase orders separately by the respective mailing IDs: **Purchase Order: printed format of a purchase order entered on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] form. **Subcontract: printed format of a subcontract entered on the [HelpRoot_Construction\SC_30_10_00|Subcontracts] form. *Subcontracts do not utilize the purchase to order process and cannot be linked to sales orders. *Subcontracts do not utilize the blanket order workflow, which is available for purchase orders.
Dedicated forms are provided for working with subcontracts:[anchor|#_3ff78970-a3c6-4fed-9dde-83c7f057cfb8] *[HelpRoot_Construction\SC_30_10_00|Subcontracts] data entry form *[HelpRoot_Construction\SC_50_30_00|Print/Email Subcontracts] ([~/?ScreenId=SC503000|SC503000]) mass-processing form
For more information on subcontract agreement forms and reports, see construction-specific reports.[anchor|#_80e4cbb0-cd29-400a-af88-61ba345aac59] ==Compliance Tracking== Firms managing construction projects have requirements to protect their clients, vendors, suppliers, and partners from the many potential issues associated with compliance. These compliance issues might be associated with federal, state and local governmental requirements, but may also be legal and procedural. Compliance tracking allows a firm to establish the compliance items that should be captured for different types of entities, so that this information can be used for in-place warnings to users and for reports on project exposure.{br}
The below types of compliance items are provided by default and can be extended with more types to track and report on:[anchor|#_3ccd0f3c-92df-48e4-bdbf-cdd292aff0f8] *''Certificate'' * ''Insurance'' * ''Lien Waiver'' * ''Notice'' * ''Other''
The user can configure common attributes that are available for all types of compliance, as well as define custom attributes for each compliance type in particular on the [HelpRoot_Construction\CL_30_10_00|'''Compliance Preferences'''] ([~/?ScreenId=CL301000|CL301000]) form. Once a compliance type is configured, the compliance items of that type can be recorded and viewed on the [HelpRoot_Construction\CL_40_10_00|Compliance Management] ([~/?ScreenId=CL401000|CL401000]) form.{br}
Each compliance item can be associated with multiple entities such as project, project task, cost code, vendor, customer, and with various types of documents. On the '''Compliance''' tab of each of the forms listed below, the users can enter and review the compliance items associated with entity:[anchor|#_e25cb398-2187-4946-ad42-2cc1884d62b2] *[HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_30_00|Vendors] ([~/?ScreenId=AP303000|AP303000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_20_00|Checks and Payments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP302000|AP302000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_30_00|Customers] ([~/?ScreenId=AR303000|AR303000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_10_00|Invoices and Memos] ([~/?ScreenId=AR301000|AR301000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] ([~/?ScreenId=PM301000|PM301000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_20_00|Project Tasks] ([~/?ScreenId=PM302000|PM302000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_40_00|Project Transactions] ([~/?ScreenId=PM304000|PM304000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) *[HelpRoot_Construction\SC_30_10_00|Subcontracts] ([~/?ScreenId=SC301000|SC301000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_80_00|Change Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PM308000|PM308000])
Based on the entered information, the system warns users of any records with compliance issues where applicable. For example, if a compliance item is overdue the system throws a warning message.[anchor|#_0eec01d4-da58-4594-bf01-38e3618e0b1f] ==Construction-Specific Reports== The following inquiries, dashboards, and reports are now available:[anchor|#_978d161b-5f3f-4caa-9238-7c320bb6010e] *'''Commitments by Vendor Summary (CU000002)''' inquiry lists vendors with open commitments (Purchase Orders/Subcontracts) within the specified date range. Commitments are totaled together to provide an order quantity, open quantity, overall total, and the open balance across all commitments. Additionally, the list can be filtered for a single project, a single vendor, and/or inventory item. Use the hyperlink within the '''Vendor ID''' and '''Vendor Name''' columns to view the line item details by open commitment. *'''Vendor Commitments Details (CU000001)''' inquiry lists open commitment line item details for the selected vendor, project, or inventory item (for example, labor, materials, subcontracts, and the like). Use the hyperlinks within the '''Account ID''', '''Project''', '''PO/Subcontract No''', '''Inventory ID''', or '''Cost Code''' columns, to obtain detailed information associated with the chosen column. For example, the hyperlink in the '''PO/Subcontract No.''' column will navigate to the Purchase Order or Subcontract form providing the user will access to available actions such as, printing or editing. *'''Project Summary (CU000003)''' inquiry provides a high-level status of the contract, costs, and gross profit. Use the hyperlinks within the '''Project''', '''Description''', and '''Open Committed Costs''' columns to obtain detailed information associated with the chosen column. For example, clicking the link in the '''Open Committed Costs''' column will navigate to the Commitments inquiry providing a detailed list of commitments for the associated project. *'''Project Dashboard (CU000013)''' dashboard. The Project Dashboard is customizable. The default configuration gives an overview of the costs by a project, contract status by a project, and gross profit by a project in a grid format. The columns of data shown in each grid can be displayed as separate widgets using a variety of chart types such as, doughnut. *'''Project WIP (CU000004)''' report provides a way to track the progress and financial performance of project contracts while using that data to forecast future performance. Drilldown goes to Project WIP Detail report. *'''Project WIP Detail (CU000005)''' report provides a way to track the progress and financial performance of project contracts while using that data to forecast future performance at a task and cost code level. *'''Subcontract Short Form (CU000006)''' report is a snapshot of the contract details broken down by a task, cost code, and inventory item. *:((({S:Warn}The report should be customized to reflect the needs of the company. ))) *'''Subcontract Agreement Long Form (CU000011)''' report is a sample of a full contract outlining the details of the agreement. *:((({S:Warn}The report should be customized to reflect the needs of the company. ))) *'''Conditional Waiver on Progress Payment (CU000008)''' report provides a sample release of partial lien rights when the current payment has not been received and future payments are expected. *'''Conditional Waiver on Final Payment (CU000007)''' report provides a sample release of the remaining lien rights when the current payment has not been received and no future payments are expected. *'''Unconditional Waiver on Progress Payment (CU000010)''' report provides a sample release of partial lien rights when the current payment has been received and future payments are expected. *'''Unconditional Waiver on Final Payment (CU000009)''' report provides a sample release of the remaining lien rights when the current payment has been received and no future payments are expected. *'''Compliance by Vendor (CU000014)''' report lists compliance items matching the report parameters in three categories: Non-Project/Commitment Items, Project/Non-Commitment related items, and Project/Commitment related items. *'''Compliance by Project (CU000012)''' report lists compliance items matching the report parameters in two categories for each project: Subcontractor(Vendor)/Non-Commitment related items and Subcontractor(Vendor)/Commitment related items. *'''Project Profit Analysis (CU000015)''' report is a snapshot of the original profit compared to the revised profit. *'''Project Performance (CU000016)''' report is a snapshot of the project performance to-date with both profit and markup values. *'''Project Cost Budget Status (CU000017)''' report provides detail into the cost budget of a project showing budgeted, committed, and actual amounts resulting in the remaining budget values per project task and overall totals for the project. Drilldown in the project column navigates to the Projects form and drilldown into the task and description columns navigates to the Project Task form. *'''Subcontract Audit (CU000018)''' report gives a snapshot of each subcontract showing the subcontract amount, changes, invoices, and outstanding balance. *'''Subcontract (SC641000)''' report displays the subcontracts created in the Subcontracts module; you can print and email them. *'''Subcontract Summary (SC610500)''' report shows summary information about subcontracts that are neither closed nor canceled. *'''Subcontract Details by Vendor (SC611000)''' report displays detailed information about subcontracts that are neither closed nor canceled. The data in this report is grouped by vendor.

A joint check is a check generated for an accounts payable bill that includes joint payees. This check is used for making a payment jointly to two or more parties. A joint check is used as a guarantee that the funds associated with the material or work provided to a contractor (subcontractor or general contractor) on a project are paid to a vendor that is not an active member of the project team.{br}
In this lesson, you will learn how to do the following:[anchor|#_01577b3f-26e2-4a96-8c20-85a28fac2f5c] *Specify joint payees for an accounts payable bill *Specify joint amounts for different lines of an accounts payable bill *Create joint checks and process the payments
==Story== Suppose that a storm broke windows in the hotel that the SweetLife company is building. The company needs to replace the broken windows and clean the area. The Acme Doors & Glass vendor will do the job for the SweetLife company. Also, they subcontracted the OfficeUp Original and Conwaste company to dispose of any waste and clean the area.{br}
At the end, SweetLife needs to issue and print a joint check that reflects the joint payment amounts. ==Process Overview== To make a joint payment, you first create an AP bill that includes joint payees on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) form. And then create and process a check for this bill on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_20_00|Checks and Payments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP302000|AP302000]) form. ==Configuration Overview== For the purposes of this lesson, the following features have been enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form:[anchor|#_4400de97-e13a-4798-8fbd-861348b0a39c] *''Construction'' (under the ''Projects'' group of features) *''Payment Application by Line''
On the '''Payment Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_30_00|Vendors] ([~/?ScreenId=AP303000|AP303000]) form, the '''Pay by Line''' check box is selected for the ''DOORSCO'' vendor. ==System Preparation== Sign in as a project manager by using the ''owen'' login and the ''123'' password. ==Step 1: Processing a Joint Bill== Do the following:[anchor|#_fa742785-635f-4638-890f-918dff014a89] #Open the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) form.[anchor|#_2075b8fe-946c-4e45-8f93-88c184f611fc] #On the form toolbar, click '''Add New Record'''. #In the '''Vendor''' box, select ''DOORSCO - Acme Doors & Glass''. #Select the '''Joint Payees''' check box. #In the '''Description''' box, type <tt>Replacing broken windows after the storm</tt>. #On the '''Document Details''' tab, add lines with the settings specified in the table below. #:{| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="16%" ! Inventory ID !width="16%" ! Quantity !width="16%" ! Unit Cost !width="16%" ! Project !width="16%" ! Cost Task !width="16%" ! Cost Code |- | ''WINDISMNTL'' | ''8'' | ''500.00'' | ''HOTEL'' | ''02'' | ''02-000'' |- | ''WINDISPOSE'' | ''4'' | ''200.00'' | ''HOTEL'' | ''02'' | ''02-000'' |- | ''WINCLEAN'' | ''4'' | ''100.00'' | ''HOTEL'' | ''02'' | ''02-000'' |} #On the '''Joint Payees''' tab, add lines with the settings specified in the table below. #:{| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="25%" ! Joint Payee (Vendor) !width="25%" ! Joint Payee !width="25%" ! Bill Line Nbr. !width="25%" ! Joint Amount Owed |- | | ''Conwaste'' | ''2'' | ''400.00'' |- | ''OFFICEUP'' | | ''3'' | ''200.00'' |} #:In the '''Bill Line Nbr.''' column, you specify the number of the bill line that corresponds to the item for which the joint payee is to receive the payment. The '''Balance''' of the line, which you can review on the '''Document Details''' tab, will be reduced by the amount specified in the '''Joint Amount Paid''' column when the payment is released. If the '''Pay by Line''' check box on the''' Financial Details''' tab is cleared for the bill, the '''Joint Amount Paid''' affects the balance of the entire bill. #:On the '''Joint Payees''' tab, you can specify a joint payee in any of the following ways: #*If the joint payee is registered in your system as a vendor, you can select that vendor in the '''Joint Payee (Vendor)''' column. #*If there is no vendor record that corresponds to the joint payee, you can simply type the name in the text box in the '''Joint Payee''' column. #:Note that the sum of the joint amounts must not be greater than or equal to the total amount of the bill. At first, the joint balance for each line equals the joint amount owed. Partial payments may be applied to the lines, and as a result, the joint balance would decrease until it is completely paid and thus reduced to zero. #Clear the '''Hold''' check box in the Summary area of the form. #Click '''Release''' on the form toolbar.
==Step 2: Processing a Joint Payment== Do the following:[anchor|#_072f670e-05b3-4dcc-bbdc-cd11532340c8] #While you are still on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) form, on the form toolbar, click '''Actions''' > '''Pay Bill/Apply Payment'''. #:The '''Indicate Amounts to Pay''' dialog box opens. #In the dialog box, do the following: ##In the '''Amount to Pay''' box, enter 400. ##:This amount defines the part of the payment that the ''Acme Doors & Glass'' vendor is going to receive. This amount cannot be greater than the amount displayed in the '''Max Available Amount''' box. ##In the '''Joint Amount to Pay''' column of the table below, enter 200 for the ''Conwaste'' joint payee and 100 for the ''OFFICEUP'' joint payee. ##Click '''Confirm'''. ##:As a result, three joint checks are created: ##*A check for 400 USD, which is the vendor payment amount ##*A check for 200 USD, which is the joint payment amount for the ''Conwaste'' joint payee ##*And a check for 100 USD, which is the joint payment amount for the ''OFFICEUP'' joint payee #On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_20_00|Checks and Payments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP302000|AP302000]) form, open each check and clear the '''Hold''' check box. #On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_50_50_00|Process Payments / Print Checks] ([~/?ScreenId=AP505000|AP505000]) form, select the unlabeled check box for each of the joint checks and click '''Process''' on the form toolbar to print the checks. #:The form that is used to print check is opened. For learning purposes, you do not need to print the checks so you can close the form. #On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_50_52_00|Release Payments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP505200|AP505200]) form, which opens, you can release the payments by clicking '''Process''' on the form toolbar. #:Note that the unlabeled check boxes are selected automatically for the corresponding payments.

The following activity will walk you through the process of configuring generation of lien waivers. ==Story== Suppose that the SweetLife company wants conditional lien waivers to be automatically generated when payments linked to AP bills are submitted. You need to configure mailing of lien waivers and their automatic generation. ==Process Overview== Brief description of workflow (with forms, on which particular actions are performed). ==System Preparation== Sign in as a project manager by using the ''owen'' login and the ''123'' password. ==Step 1: Configuring the Mailing of Lien Waivers== The processing of lien waivers includes emailing the documents to vendors who should return them signed. So that the system can generate emails with lien waivers attached, mailing should be properly configured.{br}
To configure the mailing, do the following:[anchor|#_afdbb42c-8eb8-4bef-bb8c-ad9904c257f6] #Create a notification template for lien waivers as follows: ##On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_40_03|Notification Templates] (SM2040PL) form, click '''Add New Record''' on the form toolbar. ##In the '''Screen Name''' box, select the ''Print/Email Lien Waivers (CL502000)'' form. ##In the '''Description''' box, type <tt>Lien Waivers</tt>. ##In the '''Subject''' box, type<tt> Lien waiver email</tt>. ##In the text editor area on the '''Message''' tab, specify the following text: ##:''Dear Vendor,'' ##: ''Here&rsquo;s your lien waiver.'' ##: ''Sincerely yours,'' ##: ''SweetLife'' ##Save the changes. #:When generating emails with lien waivers, the system will use the subject and the message body from the notification template. #On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_20_10_00|Vendor Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=AP201000|AP201000]) form, select the ''SUBCON'' vendor class, click the '''Mailing Settings''' tab, and do the following: ##Make sure that the ''Conditional Final'' and ''Conditional Partial'' mailings are included in the '''Mailings''' table and marked as '''Active'''. ##For each of these mailings, select the ''Lien Waiver'' notification template in the '''Notification Template''' column and in the '''Recipients''' table below, add a row with ''Remittance'' selected in the '''Contact Type''' column and default settings specified in other columns. ##Make sure that in the '''Report''' column, ''CL642003'' is specified for the ''Conditional Final'' mailing and ''CL642001 ''for the ''Conditional Partial'' mailing. These are the identifiers of the printed forms that will be generated and attached to an email. ##Save the changes. ##:These settings will be copied for any new vendor of the class. Note that mailing settings may be overridden and set up as needed for any individual vendor. When generating emails with lien waivers, the system will specify the email address of the remittance contact of the vendor (which you can review on the '''Payment Settings''' tab of the Vendors form) as the recipient address. Emails will be sent from the default system email account.
==Step 2: Configuring Automatic Generation of Lien Waivers== Do the following:[anchor|#_bbb8981e-330c-4ee3-879f-0bb7b74b4a2f] #On the '''Lien Waiver Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_Construction\CL_30_10_00|Compliance Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=CL301000|CL301000]) form, do the following: ##Select the''' Automatically Generate Lien Waivers''' check box in the '''Conditional Lien Waivers''' group of elements. ##Review the default settings and click '''Save''' on the form toolbar. ##:Because the '''Hold Documents on Entry''' check box is selected on the '''General Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_10_10_00|Accounts Payable Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=AP101000|AP101000]) form, a lien waiver will be generated when the status of the accounts payable check (or checks) changes from ''On Hold'' to ''Pending Printing'' or ''Balanced''. (If the '''Hold Documents on Entry''' check box is cleared, a lien waiver is generated immediately when the accounts payable check is created with the ''Pending Printing'' or ''Balanced'' status.) ##:The through date is set to be the last day of the posting period of the accounts payable bill. This date defines by which date the party that signs a lien waiver agrees to waive their rights for the work completed since the previous lien waiver (if any). ##:The amount of an automatically generated final conditional lien waiver will equal the amount of the accounts payable bill. #On the '''Lien Waiver Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] ([~/?ScreenId=PM301000|PM301000]) form, for the ''HOTEL'' project, review the '''Through Date''' setting and then, in the table below it, specify the following settings: #*'''Vendor Class''': ''SUBCON'' (this indicates that conditional lien waivers may be automatically generated only for vendors that belong to this vendor class) #*'''Minimum Commitment Amount''': ''2000'' (lien waivers will be automatically generated for commitments whose amount is larger than or equal to the specified minimum amount) #Save the changes. #On the '''General Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_20_10_00|Vendor Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=AP201000|AP201000]) form, for the ''SUBCON'' vendor class, select the '''Generate Lien Waivers Automatically''' check box to indicate that lien waivers will be automatically generated for vendors that belong to this vendor class. The lien waiver settings specified for the particular project will be used for generating the lien waivers. #On the '''General Info tab''' of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_30_00|Vendors] ([~/?ScreenId=AP303000|AP303000]) form, create a vendor with the following settings specified: #*'''Vendor ID''': ARCHCO #*'''Vendor Name''': Architectural Design Company #*'''Email''': main@abc.con #*'''Vendor Class''': ''SUBCON'' #Make sure that the '''Generate Lien Waivers Based on Project Settings''' check box is selected. #Save the changes.

The '''Compliance''' tab is added to multiple Acumatica ERP forms to support functionality of the applied Construction package. This topic lists altered Acumatica ERP forms and provides reference information for the '''Compliance''' tab functionality.[anchor|#_99d387eb-8b0c-4916-a1d4-27523d6ffb85] *Finance **Accounts Payable: ***[HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_30_00|Vendors] ([~/?ScreenId=AP303000|AP303000]) ***[HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) ***[HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_20_00|Checks and Payments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP302000|AP302000]) **Accounts Receivable: ***[HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_30_00|Customers] ([~/?ScreenId=AR303000|AR303000]) ***[HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_10_00|Invoices and Memos] ([~/?ScreenId=AR301000|AR301000]) *Organization **Projects: ***[HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] ([~/?ScreenId=PM301000|PM301000]) ***[HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_20_00|Project Tasks] ([~/?ScreenId=PM302000|PM302000]) ***[HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_40_00|Project Transactions] ([~/?ScreenId=PM304000|PM304000]) *Distribution **Purchase Orders: ***[HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) **Subcontracts: ***[HelpRoot_Construction\SC_30_10_00|Subcontracts] ([~/?ScreenId=SC301000|SC301000]) {br}{TOC} ==Table== The '''Compliance''' tab contains the table that lists compliance documents created by the user. The table contains only those compliance documents, which are associated with the entity that is created on the form. You can add and update compliance documents within this tab.{br}
