*'''Subcontract Number''': The number of the subcontract to be displayed. Select a number of the subcontract for which you want to build the report.

row.column:
Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=SC610500|SC610500]){br}
For a particular date range, this report shows summary information about the subcontracts that are neither closed nor canceled. The information presented for each subcontract includes the reference number, subcontract date, status, currency, vendor ID and name, ordered quantity, open quantity, line total, and open amount. The report also includes total values (for all subcontracts included in the report) for the ordered quantity, open quantity, line total, and open amount.{br}
See below for a description of each parameter on the '''Report Parameters''' tab. For more information about using other elements on the report form, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports]. ==Report Parameters== On the '''Report Parameters''' tab, use the following parameters to select the information to be displayed on the report:[anchor|#_2bcbb541-831b-479f-9a58-71e1cb87afb2] *'''Start Date''': The start date of the date range to be reported on. A start date must be selected. *'''End Date''': The end date of the date range; an end date must be selected. Only the subcontracts having dates that fall within the specified interval will be included in the report. *'''Vendor ID''': The vendor for which you want to view subcontract information, by its ID. You can select a vendor to view only subcontracts created for this vendor, or leave the box blank to view a broader range of data. *'''Inventory ID''': The non-stock item for which you want to view subcontract information. Select the ID of the non-stock to view only subcontracts created for purchasing this item.

Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=SC611000|SC611000]){br}
For a particular date range, this report displays detailed information about subcontracts that are neither closed nor canceled. The data in the report is grouped by the vendors for which the subcontracts were created.{br}
See below for a description of each parameter on the '''Report Parameters''' tab. For more information about using other elements on the report form, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports]. ==Report Parameters== On the '''Report Parameters''' tab, use the following parameters to select the information to be displayed on the report:[anchor|#_3c87c6d9-6a9a-430c-8306-65cf2a23b30f] *'''Start Date''': The start date of the date range of the report; a start date must be specified. *'''End Date''': The end date of the date range; a date must be specified here as well. Only subcontracts having dates that fall within the specified interval will be included in the report. *'''Vendor ID''': The vendor for which you want to view subcontract information, by its ID. You can select a vendor to view only subcontracts created for this vendor, or leave the box blank to view a broader range of data. *'''Inventory ID''': The non-stock item for which you want to view subcontract information. Select the inventory ID of the non-stock item to view only subcontracts created for purchasing this item.
